<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"fo=
nt-size:1.0pt;color:white">Good morning Grant, Thank you so much for your em=
ail and for sharing the process document for my claim (C90306048) at 23 Mays=
 Street, Devonport. I really appreciate
 your effort to outline the framework and the chance to work together on thi=
s.</span><span style=3D"font-size:1.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-s=
erif;color:white">=E2=80=8A</span><span style=3D"font-size:1.0pt;color:white=
"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"fo=
nt-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Good morning Grant,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Thank you so much for your email and for s=
haring the process document for my claim (C90306048) at 23 Mays Street, Devo=
nport. I really appreciate your effort to outline the framework and the chan=
ce to work together on this. It=E2=80=99s
 great to see the team involved, and I=E2=80=99d love your guidance on how w=
e can move forward smoothly.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99ve looked over the process map a=
nd have a few thoughts to ensure we get this right, especially around safety=
 and planning. I=E2=80=99ve heard from firefighters about significant fire d=
amage and smoke exiting the roof=E2=80=94initially thought
 to originate there by Devonport Flagstaff=E2=80=94which has me concerned ab=
out the house=E2=80=99s condition.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Could we please consider the following adj=
ustments?<o:p></o:p></p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Clarify Cla=
im Scope</span></strong>: Is this the plan for both house and contents claim=
s? If so, should it therefore be linked to both policy numbers to ensure all=
 coverage is included?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-m=
argin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Prioritize H=
ealth &amp; Safety</span></strong>: I=E2=80=99d feel more comfortable if we s=
cheduled independent assessments (electrical, structural, gas, moisture/moul=
d) before any major work, alongside the July 9 asbestos
 survey. The master electrician=E2=80=99s finding that the property is uninh=
abitable due to electrical hazards is a key concern.<o:p></o:p></li><li clas=
s=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;=
mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Assessment-=
Only Focus</span></strong>: As previously expressed, could we limit initial t=
asks to enabling damage assessment (e.g., securing the site, debris removal)=
 rather than repairs (e.g., upstairs decontamination,
 curtain cleaning)? This would allow for a thorough evaluation and mutual ag=
reement on remediation. The planned upstairs cleaning (July 21-25) feels pre=
mature for these reasons:
<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<ol start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1">
We need to assess damage before repair to preserve evidence.<o:p></o:p></li>=
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1">
If the gas unit (likely damaged) requires removal, the ceiling may need cutt=
ing, necessitating re-cleaning.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=
=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2 lf=
o1">
The electrician=E2=80=99s uninhabitable ruling requires electrical work firs=
t.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;m=
so-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1">
Firefighters switched off water (possibly gas?) and electricity, which must b=
e assessed and remediated.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"m=
so-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1">
With 4 pets and hybrid work, noisy basement/deck/roof work makes living ther=
e untenable until completed.<o:p></o:p></li></ol>
</ul>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Asbestos Su=
rvey Details</span></strong>: While I=E2=80=99m supportive of the July 9 sur=
vey, could you please share who will conduct it, the scope and tests involve=
d, and how I can independently verify the results?
 Also, can the funding for this be covered under the claim preparation provi=
sion?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:aut=
o;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Structural E=
ngineer Guidelines</span></strong>: I previously asked about guidelines for p=
aying a structural engineer, as per the provision for claim preparation. Cou=
ld you please provide these, as I believe
 an independent assessment should precede any repair work?<o:p></o:p></li></=
ul>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99d be grateful if you could provi=
de a revised plan with a written timeline for expert sign-offs and re-occupa=
tion only after safety is assured, preferably via email, by July 15, 2025. I=
=E2=80=99m really looking forward to working with
 you for a safe and fair outcome.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Kind regards,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Raffaella del Prete<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<div>
<blockquote style=3D"margin-top:5.0pt;margin-bottom:5.0pt">
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">On 7 Jul 2025, at 5:31<span style=3D"font-family:&quo=
t;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">=E2=80=AF</span>PM, Grant Metson &lt;<a href=3D"ma=
ilto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz">Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz</a>&gt; wrote:<o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Good evening Rafaell=
a,</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,san=
s-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Thank you for taking=
 the time to meet with me last week.</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;f=
ont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">As discussed, please=
 find attached a process document which outlines the framework of how Tower I=
nsurance will progress your claim.</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fon=
t-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">This is a framework o=
nly and the process will change, as we move through each step, given that fi=
ndings and results will affect the next step in the process. This will be a l=
ive document that will gather detail
 as we progress.</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Cal=
ibri&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">However, I do trust t=
hat this will give you some insight and knowledge to allow us to participate=
 in the process together.</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:=
&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I look forward to sp=
eaking with you soon.</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quo=
t;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Please confirm back v=
